<%= faq_schema([
  { question: "How much does a kitchen remodel cost?", answer: "National averages from Remodeling Magazine's Cost vs Value Report put a minor kitchen remodel at about 27,000 dollars and a major midrange remodel at about 77,000 dollars. Per square foot, that is roughly 150 dollars for minor cosmetic work, 225 dollars for midrange, 350 dollars for major, and 500+ dollars for luxury. A typical 150 sq ft kitchen at midrange runs 30,000 to 40,000 dollars; at major, 50,000 to 60,000; at luxury, 80,000+." },
  { question: "What does minor vs major mean?", answer: "Minor (or cosmetic) refresh keeps the layout and cabinet boxes and replaces doors, hardware, counters, sink, faucet, and paint. Midrange replaces cabinets with stock or semi-custom, updates appliances to mid-quality, and typically keeps plumbing and electrical where they are. Major gut remodel removes everything to the studs, changes the layout, upgrades plumbing and electrical, adds an island, and installs higher-end finishes. Luxury uses custom cabinets, high-end appliances, stone counters, and premium tile." },
  { question: "Where does the money go in a kitchen remodel?", answer: "Roughly: cabinets 35 percent, appliances 15 percent, countertops 15 percent, labor 20 percent, flooring 7 percent, lighting 5 percent, other 3 percent. Custom cabinets can push the cabinet percentage to 45+. Moving plumbing adds ~2,500 dollars; moving electrical adds ~1,500. The biggest line item is almost always cabinets — upgrading from stock to semi-custom alone can add 30 percent to the total." },
  { question: "Is a kitchen remodel worth it?", answer: "Remodeling Magazine's 2024 Cost vs Value Report shows minor kitchen remodels recoup about 85 percent of cost at resale, midrange major remodels recoup about 50 percent, and luxury remodels about 35 percent. The ROI is best on minor cosmetic work. However, kitchen remodels are also the most impactful on day-to-day quality of life, and real estate value is only half the picture. If you plan to stay 5+ years, major renovations pay off in enjoyment even if not in resale price." },
  { question: "How long does a kitchen remodel take?", answer: "A minor cosmetic refresh: 2-4 weeks. Midrange semi-custom remodel: 6-10 weeks. Major gut remodel: 12-20 weeks, with design and permit time adding 4-8 weeks before work starts. Custom cabinets alone take 8-12 weeks to build from order. Supply chain issues and permit delays regularly stretch projects by 4-8 weeks beyond the initial estimate." }
]) %>

